      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Laptop for School</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Murray Cartan letter, commenting on Aug 10 article, notes method used by St Mary's University in San Antonio to solve the problem of supplying computers to college students</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>St. Mary's University in San Antonio has a simple solution to the problem of supplying computers to college students (''PC 101: Pitfalls to Avoid,'' Aug. 10). It furnishes each freshman with identical laptops, with the cost included in the tuition. Each student can trade in the laptop for a newer model after two years. At graduation, each student can purchase the second laptop for $1.</p>
        <p>MURRAY CARTAN  Queens</p>
      </block>
